1
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:42,500
GYEONGGI POLICE
WITH SAFETY, ORDER, AND RESPONSIBILITY

2
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:58,808
MISSING PERSON
NAME: AN YU-YEON

3
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:01,519
That's too blurry.

4
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:03,354
That won't be enough

5
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:07,108
for us to confirm if the woman next to him

6
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:09,069
is the missing woman or not.

7
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:11,571
You guys have good eyes.
Take a closer look.

8
00:01:11,654 --> 00:01:14,824
If it were the older cameras,
it would've been more blurry.

9
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:16,910
Young-soo kept pushing for them too.

10
00:01:16,993 --> 00:01:18,036
It's blurry,

11
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:20,789
but the vehicle was spotted

12
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:23,208
{\an8}around the locations
where the women went missing.

13
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:24,250
Detective Nam.

14
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,961
-Did you run the license plate?
-I put in a request.

15
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:30,715
We used the security cameras
to track him on the same night.

16
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:33,718
But we couldn't track him
after the 5km mark.

17
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:37,472
We can suspect that he probably

18
00:01:38,306 --> 00:01:39,641
went to someplace secluded.

19
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:41,017
If he's our guy,

20
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:44,312
he probably abandoned the body right away.

21
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:52,987
Yes?

22
00:01:53,863 --> 00:01:55,031
Woo Ho-sung?

23
00:01:56,574 --> 00:01:57,742
Okay.

24
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,120
A 38-year-old man, Woo Ho-sung.

25
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:02,372
They faxed us the information
of the vehicle owner.

26
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,289
Okay.

27
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:11,756
The vehicle owner is Woo Ho-sung,
a 38-year-old man.

28
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,342
He works at an acupressure massage parlor.

29
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:17,929
Why does he look so normal?
This is so creepy.

30
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:21,432
Those who look normal
are good at scamming people.

31
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:23,393
Shouldn't we check his alibi first?

32
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,270
I'll take Detective Nam with me.

33
00:02:25,353 --> 00:02:27,397
-Okay.
-Then can you pay attention

34
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,859
to his reaction
when you meet him for the first time?

35
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:33,236
-Sure.
-I already know.

36
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,863
I bet he'll say he didn't do it.

37
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:36,531
He'll probably deny everything

38
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:37,824
even if he did it.

39
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,701
Right. He'll deny it.

40
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:41,703
So Captain Yoon,

41
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,290
I need you to check if he gets angry
or remains calm when you question him.

42
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:48,835
Pay attention to the subtle changes
in his attitude or the way he talks.

43
00:02:49,377 --> 00:02:51,629
It will help us
with our interrogation strategy.

44
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:53,256
You got it.

45
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:56,926
To women, he's still a stranger.

46
00:02:57,468 --> 00:02:59,137
No matter how approachable he seems,

47
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:01,639
they would still be hesitant
to get in his car, right?

48
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:02,807
Right.

49
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,393
And women tend to be more cautious,
especially at night,

50
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:07,687
no matter how kind they seem.

51
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:09,314
If he didn't force them to get in,

52
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:13,067
it's likely that he made them feel guilty

53
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:15,612
about turning down his kindness.

54
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,448
He made them feel guilty
by pretending to be kind?

55
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,033
This bastard is unbelievable.

56
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:22,327
This guy could skip town for all we know.

57
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:24,120
-So be careful.
-Okay.

58
00:03:24,203 --> 00:03:25,496
We'll be back.

59
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,290
Call us if there's anything.

60
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:28,875
-Okay.
-We'll call you.

61
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,376
-Thank you.
-Sure.

62
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,435
I think this is the place.

63
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:49,479
-I'll check if there's an exit.
-Okay.

64
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:50,563
ROYAL ACUPRESSURE, ANSAN, GYEONGGI

65
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:58,154
None, right?

66
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,614
This is the only exit.

67
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:01,032
Okay. Let's go inside.

68
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:05,328
-Hello.
-Welcome.

69
00:04:07,622 --> 00:04:08,873
Do you have an appointment?

70
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:11,709
We're from Wide-Area Investigation Squad.

71
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,837
Our business isn't illegal.

72
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,423
We're here to see Mr. Woo Ho-sung.

73
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:18,508
He's here, right?

74
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,636
Why do the police want to see him?

75
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,471
Could you bring him out?

76
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:26,140
He's with a customer now.

77
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:27,934
Then we'll wait here.

78
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:32,480
But your customers will come and go.
You're okay with that, right?

79
00:04:33,564 --> 00:04:34,607
Please wait.

80
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:36,818
Sure.

81
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:45,576
There.

82
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,751
Is that a wig?

83
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,211
I can't see his face clearly.

84
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,754
How do his hands look to you?

85
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:01,217
You wanted to see me?

86
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,011
Mr. Woo Ho-sung?

87
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,346
Yes. That's me.

88
00:05:08,641 --> 00:05:11,102
Could we step out for a moment?
We have some questions.

89
00:05:12,228 --> 00:05:14,480
We can talk here.

90
00:05:14,564 --> 00:05:15,773
Let's do this outside.

91
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:17,775
No. I'm sorry.

92
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:19,986
My customer is waiting for me inside.

93
00:05:20,069 --> 00:05:22,822
It's fine. Let's talk here.

94
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:30,747
Where were you on February 23
from 7 p.m. to 10 p.m.?

95
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:33,124
And what were you doing that day?

96
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,045
Why do you ask?

97
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:39,297
We need to verify your alibi

98
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:41,424
for a case we're working on.

99
00:05:43,801 --> 00:05:47,388
Did I do something wrong,

100
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,223
Detective Yoon?

101
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:51,434
On the night of February 23,

102
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:54,562
a woman in her 20s went missing in Gunpo.

103
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:59,317
That's the case we're investigating now.

104
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,819
And your vehicle was caught

105
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,363
on the security camera

106
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:06,532
in the area where the victim was.

107
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,619
My goodness. I didn't know about that.

108
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:13,748
February 23… Was that Thursday?

109
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:15,416
It was last Friday.

110
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,627
I see. Friday. Then, on February 23,

111
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:21,547
my shift must have ended before 5 p.m.

112
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:22,757
Right?

113
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:27,011
Yes. That's correct. Take a look.

114
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:32,016
WOO HO-SUNG

115
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,727
-I see.
-I had dinner around here

116
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:37,855
with my girlfriend. And then I went home.

117
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:44,445
And my girlfriend also happens
to live in Gunpo.

118
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:48,366
There are dangerous people in the world.

119
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:51,452
So I can never let her go alone.
I always drop her off.

120
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:54,288
And I drove her home that night as always.

121
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,457
I don't remember the exact time,

122
00:06:56,541 --> 00:07:00,253
but I was home around 10 p.m.

123
00:07:02,463 --> 00:07:05,716
Could we get your girlfriend's

124
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,301
phone number?

125
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,762
I can't.

126
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,975
Am I obligated by law
to give you her number?

127
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,064
I don't want my girlfriend to worry.

128
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:23,734
Then how about this?

129
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:27,321
You can check my alibi
at the restaurant we went to that day.

130
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:28,990
I made a reservation before going.

131
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:33,411
Check it yourself.

132
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:36,414
What if we go there and ask them, but…

133
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:37,999
Go check first.

134
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:40,251
If you still can't confirm my alibi,

135
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:42,962
I'll give you her number then.

136
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:46,007
Is that all?

137
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:48,426
I have to get back in.

138
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:52,763
Thank you for your cooperation.

139
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:53,931
You're welcome.

140
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,689
-Thank you. Take care.
-You too.

141
00:08:02,607 --> 00:08:04,525
I'm so sorry to keep you waiting.

142
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:07,111
I'll give you ten extra minutes

143
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:09,739
to make up for it.

144
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:36,224
If we combed through the entire area
but didn't find additional bodies,

145
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,768
it means he buried them elsewhere.

146
00:08:38,851 --> 00:08:41,437
Like the sixth case, it must be a place
that can't easily be found.

147
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,856
We have to ask him about it
when we interrogate him.

148
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:47,568
The sixth victim, Yoon Jin-sil,
was abducted in Anyang.

149
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:51,697
Then Woo Ho-sung buried her
on his way home to Ansan.

150
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,617
And his place isn't far from the bank
where money was withdrawn

151
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,452
from the account of An Yu-yeon,
the seventh victim.

152
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:59,622
He doesn't live far from
where the other victims went missing,

153
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:01,958
assuming that he was driving.

154
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:04,794
And his vehicle was caught on camera,

155
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:07,255
heading in the same direction
that the culprit must've gone.

156
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:11,050
Woo Ho-sung is our prime suspect.

157
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,887
Woo Ho-sung, that scumbag.

158
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:18,015
It's possible
he's also committed insurance scams.

159
00:09:23,479 --> 00:09:25,898
<i>I'm Detective Nam from
the Gyeonggi Provincial Police Agency.</i>

160
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:28,859
Did someone named Woo Ho-sung
have a reservation here?

161
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:31,988
Woo Ho-sung? What's his phone number?

162
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:34,448
That is him.

163
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:35,825
WOO HO-SUNG

164
00:09:39,161 --> 00:09:40,705
Yes, Gyeonggi Provincial Police Agency…

165
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:42,999
It's Detective Yoon.

166
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,626
Hang on. Let me put you on speaker.

167
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:49,422
Go ahead.

168
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:51,757
Does he have an alibi?

169
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,217
He said he had dinner

170
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:55,136
with his girlfriend that evening.

171
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:58,180
<i>After that, he drove her home.</i>

172
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:00,933
Detective Nam went
to the restaurant to check.

173
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:02,935
What's his attitude like?

174
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,186
He seemed self-assured.

175
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,106
And he's confident.

176
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:10,234
<i>He also seemed relaxed.</i>

177
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:14,155
He sounds polite and has good manners,

178
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:16,741
so I can see the victims
letting their guard down easily

179
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:20,786
after a few awkward moments
upon encountering a stranger.

180
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,913
You haven't checked his car, have you?

181
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:24,915
We can't search his car without a warrant.

182
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:28,919
If we aren't careful,
he may try to destroy evidence,

183
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:32,048
so we'll wait until he gets off work
and check naturally

184
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:33,341
when he gets in his car.

185
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:40,389
How did it go?

186
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:42,975
He was at the restaurant that evening.

187
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:47,188
He did have a reservation under his name,
and I checked the CCTV footage too.

188
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:49,690
The woman he was with
wasn't the one who went missing.

189
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,484
I think it was his girlfriend.

190
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:57,531
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

191
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:03,412
Wait, Ho-sung.

192
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,373
What did the detectives want?

193
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,708
I think there was a misunderstanding.

194
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:09,794
How could they suspect you, of all people?

195
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,797
-It's all cleared up now.
-Good.

196
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:23,641
He's different from those who don't have

197
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:27,311
the ability to lure their victims or those
who launch random motiveless attacks.

198
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:31,524
On top of his expensive car
and likable face,

199
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:34,151
he has a way with words.
He used all those things

200
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:36,821
to find and lure his victims.

201
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:38,948
He knows that it works.

202
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:42,326
That's where
Woo Ho-sung's confidence comes from.

203
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,494
That's right.

204
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,581
Yes, Wide-Area Investigation Squad…

205
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:49,166
Hey.

206
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,167
Hold on.

207
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:52,253
Go ahead.

208
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:55,297
<i>We have confirmed his alibi
that he had dinner</i>

209
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,924
<i>with his girlfriend that evening.</i>

210
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:59,301
Do we know what else he did that night?

211
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:01,887
Detective Moon at Anyang Station
looked into it,

212
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:05,057
but there was nothing on his call log
after 7 p.m. that evening.

213
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:09,728
<i>We checked all the cameras near his home,</i>

214
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,605
<i>and he got home at around 1:00 a.m.</i>

215
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:17,778
He told us that he got home
at around 10 p.m.

216
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:22,908
We need to go and check.
I wish we could search his house now.

217
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,660
Our priority is securing evidence.

218
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:27,955
If we put in a request
for a search and seizure warrant now,

219
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:30,249
the prosecutors will laugh at us.

220
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,418
-It won't be issued.
-<i>Chief Park.</i>

221
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:35,421
We'll wait here
until Woo Ho-sung gets off work

222
00:12:35,504 --> 00:12:37,214
and ask him to voluntarily
come into the station.

223
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:38,883
I'll call you back.

224
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:42,470
Goodness.

225
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:44,346
Even if we request a warrant now,

226
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,974
we won't get it tonight.

227
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,857
Okay, fine.

228
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,109
I'll speak with Superintendent Heo.

229
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:59,528
I'm getting a bad feeling.

230
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:00,821
NAME: WOO HO-SUNG

231
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:04,533
We need a search and seizure warrant
for Woo Ho-sung's vehicle and residence.

232
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,702
We must secure evidence
as soon as possible.

233
00:13:07,953 --> 00:13:10,789
It's also possible he committed
insurance scams in the past.

234
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:13,292
Insurance scams? What did he do?

235
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:15,294
In 2005,

236
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:18,047
his wife and mother-in-law died in a fire.

237
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:21,675
The life insurance payout he got
was 400 million won in total.

238
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:22,676
400 million won?

239
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:26,805
He had signed up
for various life insurance policies.

240
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:29,767
But the insurance companies
must've deemed it legitimate for him

241
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,268
to have received the money.

242
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:32,770
On what grounds are we suspecting him?

243
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:37,107
Even with Gu Young-chun and Nam Ki-Tae,
we found evidence in their homes.

244
00:13:38,442 --> 00:13:41,487
We can't let this guy buy time.
Not even another moment.

245
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:43,072
He'll destroy all the evidence.

246
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:45,074
And this is

247
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:49,161
Song Ha-young's profiling report.

248
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,624
{\an8}GYEONGGI SERIAL MISSING WOMEN CASE
PROFILING REPORT

249
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:57,503
Everyone now knows he was instrumental
in tracking down Gu Young-chun

250
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:58,921
and Nam Ki-Tae.

251
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,966
You should submit this
along with the request.

252
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,552
Okay, I'll speak with Prosecutor Jang.

253
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:08,055
But I highly doubt
that it'll be issued today.

254
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:12,643
POMNA DRY CLEANING

255
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:14,186
Should I go pick up some snacks?

256
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,437
I guess you're hungry.

257
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,356
A little.

258
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:22,903
Go ahead.

259
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:25,990
-Okay.
-Wait, Detective Nam.

260
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:31,370
ROYAL ACUPRESSURE MASSAGE

261
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:55,686
Mr. Woo Ho-sung!

262
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:04,987
Do you still have more questions for me?

263
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,614
We believe it'll take a while.

264
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:07,823
Could we talk

265
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:10,367
at the station?

266
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:13,037
Are you arresting me now?

267
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:18,375
Can I see the warrant?

268
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:19,960
We're asking you
to voluntarily come with us.

269
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,795
You may refuse if you don't want to.

270
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:23,881
But if you refuse,

271
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:26,592
it will make us more suspicious of you.

272
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:30,679
We'll continue to keep
a close watch on you.

273
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:41,106
Okay, fine.
I'll come in and give a statement.

274
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,525
-Then let's take our--
-The thing is,

275
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:47,029
I was booked back-to-back today,
so I'm very tired right now.

276
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:49,073
But I'm off tomorrow,

277
00:15:49,156 --> 00:15:52,117
so may I visit the station
sometime tomorrow morning?

278
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:10,803
Sure.

279
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,597
Please come…

280
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:16,350
to the Gyeonggi Provincial Police Agency.

281
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:18,936
-If you don't come…
-I know.

282
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:22,231
Why wouldn't I when I did nothing wrong?

283
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:26,151
I just have to
ask for Detective Yoon, right?

284
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:28,320
-Yes.
-Okay.

285
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:30,906
I'll see you tomorrow.

286
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,411
See you tomorrow.

287
00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:49,967
I saw…

288
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:53,345
a photo of him with two dogs in his car.

289
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:55,931
And there was a huge teddy bear
in the back seat.

290
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:57,599
Just as we expected.

291
00:16:57,683 --> 00:17:00,310
As you said, he's too calm.

292
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:01,603
He'll come tomorrow, right?

293
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:03,772
If he flees, it's him for sure,
so we can put out an APB.

294
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,811
Good work today. Let's call it a night.

295
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:46,732
GYEONGGI PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

296
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:49,943
I can't stop thinking
that he's the culprit.

297
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:55,240
He fits every quality
of the suspect we presumed.

298
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,159
He's amicable and has good manners.

299
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:58,327
He even has a nice car.

300
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,329
He even has a luring mechanism in his car.

301
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:03,207
He's under suspicion
of arson and insurance fraud.

302
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:06,168
We have to be open to the possibility
he's proficient in arson.

303
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:09,838
There's no perp
who only commits one crime.

304
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:12,341
All we need is the warrant.

305
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:17,763
I'm sure he was psychologically pressured.

306
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:25,414
GYEONGGI PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

307
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:52,232
Wide-Area Investigation Squad,
Gyeonggi Provincial Police Agency.

308
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:54,776
<i>May I speak to Detective Yoon Tae-gu?</i>

309
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:58,197
Who's calling?

310
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,743
I'm the guy
who was supposed to meet her today.

311
00:20:02,826 --> 00:20:05,537
If she's in the office,
could you put her on?

312
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:11,084
She's not in the office. If you leave
a message, I'll relay it to her.

313
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:14,504
Hello?

314
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:17,466
-Hello?
<i>-In that case, I'll call back…</i>

315
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:19,718
One second, she just came in.
I'll put her on right away.

316
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:21,845
Captain Yoon, it's Woo Ho-sung.

317
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,186
I'm on the line.
You've reached Yoon Tae-gu.

318
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:31,855
Hello. This is Woo Ho-sung.

319
00:20:33,607 --> 00:20:34,566
Mr. Woo Ho-sung.

320
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:42,574
<i>Do you take a report like this
at Wide-Area Investigation?</i>

321
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:47,579
Someone set my car on fire.

322
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:54,544
Sorry?

323
00:20:55,545 --> 00:20:57,089
What do you mean?

324
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:02,177
Does Wide-Area Investigation Squad
take reports like this?

325
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:22,906
I thought he was a pretty smart guy,
but he wasn't.

326
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:24,992
He's just feeling guilty.

327
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:29,246
We got the warrant more quickly
thanks to his show.

328
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:30,956
It's nice.

329
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,960
And the profiling report
also played a part.

330
00:21:35,043 --> 00:21:38,672
WOO HO-SUNG'S HOME

331
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:48,098
As of this hour,

332
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:52,602
we will begin the search and seizure
of every article in your house.

333
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:56,315
Also, Woo Ho-sung.

334
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:59,401
You are under emergency arrest
for suspicions of abduction.

335
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:03,322
You should be looking for the person
who set my car on fire.

336
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:07,034
Why are you arresting me?

337
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:10,287
You have the right to an attorney,

338
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:12,456
and you have the right to remain silent.

339
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:17,961
Everything you say can and will be

340
00:22:19,212 --> 00:22:22,341
used to the extreme disadvantage
against you in court.

341
00:22:22,424 --> 00:22:23,550
Do you understand?

342
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:29,139
Just as I expected, he's confident.

343
00:22:29,639 --> 00:22:32,642
He knew we'd get suspicious of him
for setting his car on fire.

344
00:22:32,726 --> 00:22:34,603
But he still chose to do that
to get rid of the evidence.

345
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:38,273
We pressured him to go talk
at the police station,

346
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:40,317
so he got anxious
and made the wrong choice.

347
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:43,070
I think he wanted to play the victim.

348
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:47,866
But he was in a hurry, so he must have
resorted to something he was used to.

349
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:52,537
He forgot that he was under suspicion
of arson and insurance fraud.

350
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:57,918
Does he think the police are a joke?
As if we wouldn't have looked into it.

351
00:22:58,001 --> 00:23:00,962
I guess he does think
he's smarter than others.

352
00:23:01,046 --> 00:23:02,631
He tripped over his own feet.

353
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,424
Let's go inside.

354
00:23:08,011 --> 00:23:10,263
You haven't figured out anything.

355
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:13,767
Why don't you undo this
before we start talking?

356
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:33,662
The fingers that punched in

357
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,622
the PIN at the ATM to withdraw money.

358
00:23:36,998 --> 00:23:37,999
It's similar

359
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:39,751
to Woo Ho-sung's hand.

360
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:40,919
Did you see it?

361
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:44,631
<i>When I went to the massage parlor
and when I cuffed him.</i>

362
00:23:44,714 --> 00:23:45,674
I saw his hands.

363
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:47,551
Woo Ho-sung is also conscious of that.

364
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:50,887
It looks like it.

365
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:53,807
Are other detectives watching me

366
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:56,434
from behind that wall?

367
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:58,186
You know why you're here, right?

368
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,980
How many of you are there?

369
00:24:01,356 --> 00:24:03,483
Didn't you hear me?
I asked you a question.

370
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:06,611
I'm not sure.

371
00:24:07,362 --> 00:24:09,364
She told you when she cuffed you.

372
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:10,323
Abduction.

373
00:24:10,407 --> 00:24:13,118
Who? Who did I abduct?

374
00:24:13,201 --> 00:24:15,203
You would know better than us.

375
00:24:18,456 --> 00:24:19,708
Do you have evidence?

376
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,502
That's why we arrested you.

377
00:24:22,586 --> 00:24:25,130
Even if you search through my house,

378
00:24:25,213 --> 00:24:27,007
you won't find anything.

379
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:37,517
SCIENTIFIC INVESTIGATIONS

380
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:39,060
Did you find anything?

381
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:40,896
I don't see anything in particular.

382
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,990
He formatted everything.

383
00:24:52,616 --> 00:24:55,160
This is you, isn't it?

384
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:56,244
CCTV FOOTAGE EVIDENCE

385
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:58,872
What is this?

386
00:24:58,955 --> 00:25:02,959
You used the debit card of a woman
who went missing and withdrew cash.

387
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,129
Show me

388
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:09,382
the evidence that this is me.

389
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,219
Where is that woman?

390
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:13,762
Who?

391
00:25:13,845 --> 00:25:15,680
This is you.

392
00:25:15,764 --> 00:25:16,848
Where is she?

393
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:21,186
I really have no idea
what you're talking about.

394
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:23,313
At 2 p.m. on February 24,

395
00:25:23,396 --> 00:25:24,731
tell me where you were.

396
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:32,822
I slept at home.

397
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:34,824
Not that. Give me something else.

398
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:37,661
Something more feasible.

399
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:42,958
I said I slept at home.

400
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:45,710
Do you expect me to believe
that you were asleep in broad daylight?

401
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,462
In this situation?

402
00:25:47,545 --> 00:25:50,465
What would I do on weekends?
I should sleep.

403
00:25:50,548 --> 00:25:52,300
You said you had a girlfriend.

404
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:55,053
If anything,
you would've gone out on a date.

405
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,347
We went out the day before.

406
00:25:58,390 --> 00:25:59,933
I need a day to rest.

407
00:26:00,767 --> 00:26:02,102
It was my day off too.

408
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:06,690
You don't know who I am, do you?

409
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,610
This is you. I know it is.

410
00:26:12,279 --> 00:26:13,488
Do you have evidence?

411
00:26:15,699 --> 00:26:17,492
If you don't, you have to believe me.

412
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:27,669
The dead karaoke bar employee

413
00:26:28,378 --> 00:26:31,589
found on that hill
was probably killed by him too, right?

414
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:32,924
I believe so.

415
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:35,510
The dead body had traces of rape too.

416
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:38,555
We must get him to confess
to the sexual assault too.

417
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:42,017
How did he seem?
Is he a little different now?

418
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,145
He did not show any emotional distress.

419
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:48,940
He seemed rather calm
in a startling situation.

420
00:26:49,024 --> 00:26:51,401
It looks like he has
an antisocial personality disorder.

421
00:26:51,484 --> 00:26:52,694
Like a psychopath?

422
00:26:53,486 --> 00:26:56,239
-Yes.
-Someone extremely self-centered,

423
00:26:58,158 --> 00:26:59,659
who lacks a sense of sympathy

424
00:27:00,744 --> 00:27:01,953
and a guilty conscience.

425
00:27:02,037 --> 00:27:05,373
It looked like he kept two dogs.

426
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:07,250
It's probably a cover-up.

427
00:27:07,334 --> 00:27:10,754
<i>I'm sure he only used them
to lure the victims.</i>

428
00:27:11,629 --> 00:27:13,631
Let's conduct the PCL-R on him later.

429
00:27:14,257 --> 00:27:16,634
He seems to be the type
to show aggression selectively.

430
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:17,802
What do you mean?

431
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:21,348
People like him have
a high level of self-control.

432
00:27:21,431 --> 00:27:23,641
They keep their composure until the moment

433
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:26,227
of their crime.
They won't show their emotions.

434
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,188
But once he begins to attack,

435
00:27:29,356 --> 00:27:31,441
he becomes more brutal
and violent than others.

436
00:27:32,275 --> 00:27:34,736
Are you saying
he picks and chooses his victims?

437
00:27:34,819 --> 00:27:35,904
You're right.

438
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:37,572
Gu Young-chun and Nam Ki-Tae

439
00:27:37,655 --> 00:27:41,284
expressed their aggression
toward many unspecified people.

440
00:27:42,118 --> 00:27:43,620
But that man

441
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:46,623
only expresses his aggression
toward the victims he chose.

442
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:51,378
I think we should be more strategic
about our interrogation tactics.

443
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:56,257
Even if we show him evidence,
he won't confess that easily.

444
00:27:56,341 --> 00:27:58,093
Chief Kook and I will interrogate him.

445
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:07,435
Two gentlemen are joining me this time.

446
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:10,897
Are you here
to have a conversation with me?

447
00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:13,358
That's right.

448
00:28:15,151 --> 00:28:18,530
What about
the other detectives from earlier?

449
00:28:18,613 --> 00:28:20,407
You'll be talking to us for a while.

450
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:24,869
I told you to get evidence.

451
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:27,247
I guess it's not going well.

452
00:28:30,417 --> 00:28:31,668
Gosh.

453
00:28:34,129 --> 00:28:36,089
If you wanted to talk to me,

454
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:39,884
you should have at least
brought me some water.

455
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:41,177
Is that all you need?

456
00:28:46,349 --> 00:28:48,601
We're here to talk to you.

457
00:28:48,685 --> 00:28:50,770
But we're not here to bring you water.

458
00:28:51,938 --> 00:28:54,274
Let us know once you actually get thirsty.

459
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:56,651
I'll get you some water then.

460
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:01,614
What are they doing?

461
00:29:02,949 --> 00:29:06,202
Just let them do their thing.
They have their own system.

462
00:29:07,495 --> 00:29:10,623
His attitude seems
a bit different from before.

463
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:11,708
Whose attitude?

464
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,878
-Song Ha-young's?
-Yes.

465
00:29:14,961 --> 00:29:16,379
Rightfully so.

466
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:19,174
After all, he went through a lot.

467
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,472
<i>This guy is different.</i>

468
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:29,017
<i>He probably subdued the victims
in a matter of seconds</i>

469
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:30,977
<i>and clouded their emotional judgment.</i>

470
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:33,188
<i>Then he probably continued his act</i>

471
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:36,858
<i>just like he was trying to have
a power struggle by making me bring water.</i>

472
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:43,072
I've been sitting here

473
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:45,950
and talking to the detectives
since I got here.

474
00:29:46,034 --> 00:29:47,744
What else do you want to talk about?

475
00:29:47,827 --> 00:29:49,871
We have our own set of questions.

476
00:29:49,954 --> 00:29:51,206
If you have time for this,

477
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:55,376
wouldn't it be better spent
looking for evidence outside?

478
00:29:56,461 --> 00:29:58,505
All you're doing is sitting here…

479
00:30:01,758 --> 00:30:03,092
and running your mouth.

480
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:05,804
We're looking for evidence.
So don't worry about it.

481
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:07,639
All right. If you say so.

482
00:30:07,722 --> 00:30:09,516
It won't take long to find evidence.

483
00:30:11,392 --> 00:30:14,687
Why is that jerk so brazen?

484
00:30:14,771 --> 00:30:17,941
You know denying their charges
shamelessly is their specialty.

485
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:19,609
According to Chief Kook,

486
00:30:19,692 --> 00:30:21,486
his self-control is very high.

487
00:30:22,403 --> 00:30:26,032
And it looks like he's trying
to control his emotions even now.

488
00:30:26,115 --> 00:30:28,827
He asked for water as soon as he saw them

489
00:30:28,910 --> 00:30:31,955
to test whether or not
he could control them.

490
00:30:32,038 --> 00:30:34,082
Does he think he can intimidate them?

491
00:30:34,582 --> 00:30:35,959
How dare he?

492
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:38,211
Let me ask you a few questions.

493
00:30:39,629 --> 00:30:41,214
Your wife and mother-in-law died

494
00:30:41,965 --> 00:30:43,633
in a fire a few years ago.

495
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:48,388
And you only took your son
when you escaped.

496
00:30:50,056 --> 00:30:52,934
When you think about it again,
how do you feel?

497
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:02,694
Why must I think about that now?

498
00:31:02,777 --> 00:31:06,406
I'm just asking how you feel
or what you're thinking right now.

499
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:07,991
I don't know

500
00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:12,912
how the fire has anything
to do with this incident.

501
00:31:15,540 --> 00:31:17,083
Why are you bringing up my son?

502
00:31:18,209 --> 00:31:19,252
Your son?

503
00:31:21,838 --> 00:31:25,091
I wonder how your son would feel
once he finds out that his dad is

504
00:31:25,675 --> 00:31:27,093
a serial murderer and rapist.

505
00:31:29,596 --> 00:31:30,722
You see,

506
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:33,766
he's too young to know anything.

507
00:31:34,350 --> 00:31:35,643
Not yet.

508
00:31:37,395 --> 00:31:39,105
No. Listen.

509
00:31:39,939 --> 00:31:42,108
Nothing has been proven yet.

510
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:45,236
I really don't follow you.

511
00:31:46,779 --> 00:31:48,114
That's right.

512
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:50,491
"Not yet."

513
