00:46:14,813 --> 00:46:16,273
We need to get a confession out of him.

772
00:46:40,923 --> 00:46:42,925
Goodness.

773
00:46:46,178 --> 00:46:47,346
We found something.

774
00:46:49,056 --> 00:46:51,099
This is what
we've been eagerly waiting for.

775
00:46:51,934 --> 00:46:53,018
DNA ANALYSIS REPORT

776
00:46:53,101 --> 00:46:54,061
The evidence.

777
00:46:55,812 --> 00:46:57,189
It's the victim's DNA…

778
00:46:58,273 --> 00:47:00,108
that we found from your clothes.

779
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:02,986
We found it.

780
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:04,404
BELONGS TO THE SAME PERSON

781
00:47:20,671 --> 00:47:23,215
HEO GEUM-YOUNG

782
00:47:24,591 --> 00:47:26,343
WORKS AT YEONJIN CHINESE RESTAURANT

783
00:47:26,426 --> 00:47:28,262
HEO GEUM-YOUNG, 51

784
00:47:28,345 --> 00:47:30,430
{\an8}SPECIMEN 1 AND 2 BELONG TO THE SAME PERSON

785
00:47:30,514 --> 00:47:32,182
Captain Yoon, the one who just left.

786
00:47:34,268 --> 00:47:36,270
Ask her to come in.

787
00:47:37,563 --> 00:47:41,650
Stop trying to conjure up a trick.
Just confess, you scumbag.

788
00:47:43,610 --> 00:47:44,945
I will confess.

789
00:47:46,738 --> 00:47:48,073
In return,

790
00:47:50,534 --> 00:47:52,703
I want Captain Yoon here.

791
00:47:54,162 --> 00:47:56,540
I'll go get a confession out of him.

792
00:47:57,624 --> 00:47:58,750
Hold on.

793
00:47:59,334 --> 00:48:00,836
I'll go in first.

794
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:05,257
-You?
-I want to say something to Woo Ho-sung.

795
00:48:06,842 --> 00:48:09,553
-It'll be quick.
-Sure, go ahead.

796
00:48:10,137 --> 00:48:12,014
-Will you be all right?
-Yes.

797
00:48:13,015 --> 00:48:14,266
I'll go in myself.

798
00:48:28,363 --> 00:48:29,239
How do you feel?

799
00:48:31,992 --> 00:48:33,285
About what?

800
00:48:33,368 --> 00:48:35,245
You have nowhere to run now.

801
00:48:35,329 --> 00:48:37,331
You're good at finding evidence.

802
00:48:37,414 --> 00:48:40,083
Science is much smarter than you think.

803
00:48:41,126 --> 00:48:42,919
So is the quality of our investigation.

804
00:48:44,546 --> 00:48:47,132
That perfect crime you want?
There's no such thing.

805
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,385
Woo Ho-sung.

806
00:48:52,971 --> 00:48:55,474
-Be smart about it.
-About what?

807
00:48:55,557 --> 00:48:57,142
Whether or not
you want your son to remember you

808
00:48:57,225 --> 00:48:59,227
as an unremorseful murderer
until the very end.

809
00:49:00,062 --> 00:49:02,147
And this will be the last time we talk.

810
00:49:04,608 --> 00:49:05,776
I'm not scared.

811
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:07,611
I'm not saying this to scare you.

812
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:12,407
I'm telling you that
nobody will listen to your story anymore.

813
00:49:14,701 --> 00:49:16,620
I already know
that there are multiple victims.

814
00:49:17,204 --> 00:49:18,372
We have the evidence too.

815
00:49:21,041 --> 00:49:22,959
I thought you weren't here
to talk about the case.

816
00:49:23,043 --> 00:49:25,671
-I'm not.
-Then let's change the subject.

817
00:49:25,754 --> 00:49:28,715
No. I already have you figured out.

818
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:34,137
Which is why I'm no longer curious.

819
00:50:05,961 --> 00:50:08,088
Would it be possible…

820
00:50:10,882 --> 00:50:12,801
for me to talk privately
with Captain Yoon?

821
00:50:16,638 --> 00:50:17,597
I'll be fine.

822
00:50:20,642 --> 00:50:21,852
Give me your hands.

823
00:50:34,489 --> 00:50:36,074
What is it that you want to say?

824
00:50:38,160 --> 00:50:39,202
I'm sure…

825
00:50:40,662 --> 00:50:42,622
getting a confession out of someone

826
00:50:45,709 --> 00:50:47,627
is harder
than you detectives think, right?

827
00:50:49,504 --> 00:50:51,381
It's the same for the confessor too.

828
00:50:52,924 --> 00:50:53,967
Which is why…

829
00:50:54,843 --> 00:50:55,927
I'm torn.

830
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:02,267
<i>Whether the culprit confesses or not</i>

831
00:51:03,393 --> 00:51:04,770
is his decision to make.

832
00:51:04,853 --> 00:51:05,979
Then how…

833
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:09,316
can I get him to decide?

834
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:12,527
Just give the nuance
that you understand him to an extent.

835
00:51:13,028 --> 00:51:15,155
Woo Ho-sung
has strong narcissistic tendencies.

836
00:51:15,781 --> 00:51:17,240
If you form a rapport with him,

837
00:51:18,074 --> 00:51:19,993
it'll bring about a change
in his emotions.

838
00:51:21,703 --> 00:51:23,288
Don't you think…

839
00:51:25,999 --> 00:51:28,502
the burden will be lifted
once you confess?

840
00:51:29,669 --> 00:51:30,921
Whose burden?

841
00:51:31,004 --> 00:51:32,088
Yours.

842
00:51:33,423 --> 00:51:34,508
And mine too.

843
00:51:35,884 --> 00:51:37,093
Do you really think so?

844
00:51:37,636 --> 00:51:38,970
I'm sure…

845
00:51:40,222 --> 00:51:43,183
you had a reason
why you asked for me specifically.

846
00:51:46,478 --> 00:51:48,438
Whatever it is that you have to tell me,

847
00:51:49,940 --> 00:51:51,441
I'm ready to listen

848
00:51:53,068 --> 00:51:53,902
to you.

849
00:52:05,705 --> 00:52:06,623
Why did you do it?

850
00:52:13,004 --> 00:52:14,881
Must there always…

851
00:52:16,967 --> 00:52:18,051
be a reason

852
00:52:20,554 --> 00:52:22,097
why you kill someone?

853
00:52:24,224 --> 00:52:25,183
So…

854
00:52:26,977 --> 00:52:28,520
you didn't have a reason?

855
00:52:29,312 --> 00:52:31,648
Well, if I had to come up with one,

856
00:52:36,027 --> 00:52:37,654
it's because I wanted to kill them.

857
00:52:38,405 --> 00:52:39,698
How many…

858
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:41,616
did you murder?

859
00:52:45,704 --> 00:52:46,913
We found…

860
00:52:47,706 --> 00:52:50,500
components of another victim's lipstick

861
00:52:52,043 --> 00:52:53,086
from your car.

862
00:52:54,254 --> 00:52:56,590
It will all be revealed in the end.

863
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:04,681
That hand.

864
00:53:05,348 --> 00:53:07,976
You tried your best to hide your face.

865
00:53:08,059 --> 00:53:09,269
But unfortunately,

866
00:53:11,229 --> 00:53:12,939
you weren't able to hide your hand.

867
00:53:19,654 --> 00:53:21,740
You've been self-conscious
about it all along, right?

868
00:53:25,493 --> 00:53:27,454
Once you are ready to talk to me,

869
00:53:31,124 --> 00:53:32,167
I'll come back.

870
00:53:37,255 --> 00:53:38,590
All right.

871
00:53:44,596 --> 00:53:46,014
I will talk.

872
00:54:02,530 --> 00:54:04,908
<i>The suspect confessed
that he murdered all the women</i>

873
00:54:04,991 --> 00:54:08,912
<i>who started going missing in 2006
around Gyeonggi's southwestern area.</i>

874
00:54:08,995 --> 00:54:12,582
<i>Early this morning in Suwon, the police
found the body of the missing housewife.</i>

875
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:14,960
<i>They are continuing their search
for the other women's bodies…</i>

876
00:54:15,043 --> 00:54:16,461
Is this hair?

877
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,756
Oh, I found it!

878
00:54:19,839 --> 00:54:21,716
-What?
-I found something.

879
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:22,717
Look.

880
00:54:22,801 --> 00:54:24,970
<i>On the day I planned to murder,</i>

881
00:54:26,221 --> 00:54:28,682
I made sure that I executed it.

882
00:54:31,393 --> 00:54:32,644
No matter what.

883
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:36,106
You're saying you planned
for all seven murders?

884
00:54:36,189 --> 00:54:37,357
Of course.

885
00:54:38,900 --> 00:54:40,694
I'm determined from the moment

886
00:54:41,987 --> 00:54:43,196
I leave the house.

887
00:54:44,406 --> 00:54:45,573
Did you ever fail?

888
00:54:46,449 --> 00:54:47,450
Fail?

889
00:54:49,244 --> 00:54:50,495
I have never failed.

890
00:54:52,163 --> 00:54:53,248
You see,

891
00:54:54,416 --> 00:54:56,626
it's like a promise I make to myself.

892
00:54:58,420 --> 00:55:01,047
I executed it.

893
00:55:03,758 --> 00:55:05,093
One way or another.

894
00:55:05,802 --> 00:55:08,346
<i>The police intensely investigated
the suspect to find out</i>

895
00:55:08,430 --> 00:55:12,851
<i>if he committed additional crimes
until early this morning.</i>

896
00:55:12,934 --> 00:55:16,146
<i>They will also carry out
a crime scene reenactment this morning.</i>

897
00:55:16,229 --> 00:55:17,147
Look over here.

898
00:55:17,230 --> 00:55:21,776
<i>He reenacted three
out of his seven crimes yesterday.</i>

899
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:24,654
<i>The bereaved families and residents
were enraged once again</i>

900
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:27,949
<i>as they watched him
reenact the crime nonchalantly.</i>

901
00:55:29,242 --> 00:55:30,910
<i>I have always known…</i>

902
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:33,913
that I was a psychopath.

903
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:36,541
Why did you think that?

904
00:55:37,667 --> 00:55:38,918
I was watching TV one day.

905
00:55:41,129 --> 00:55:42,213
When I heard

906
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:44,716
the characteristics of a psychopath…

907
00:55:47,093 --> 00:55:48,428
I realized.

908
00:55:51,598 --> 00:55:52,849
That's me in a nutshell.

909
00:55:55,852 --> 00:55:57,562
Take his hat off. Let me see him!

910
00:55:57,645 --> 00:55:59,397
-My gosh.
-That scumbag…

911
00:55:59,481 --> 00:56:03,234
<i>His second crime was by Highway 39,
which was his secret burial site.</i>

912
00:56:03,318 --> 00:56:05,612
<i>When the police told him
to reenact how he dug the ground,</i>

913
00:56:05,695 --> 00:56:08,031
<i>he was comfortable enough
to revise the order.</i>

914
00:56:08,114 --> 00:56:10,575
<i>Saying that he dug the ground
after he took the body out of the car.</i>

915
00:56:11,159 --> 00:56:13,912
<i>His calm demeanor
as he reenacted the horrible crime</i>

916
00:56:13,995 --> 00:56:16,289
<i>made the onlookers even more furious.</i>

917
00:56:16,372 --> 00:56:19,751
<i>The bereaved families who came later
to watch the reenactment</i>

918
00:56:19,834 --> 00:56:22,337
<i>were crying out,
demanding to see his face.</i>

919
00:56:23,755 --> 00:56:26,299
When do you feel the urge to kill?

920
00:56:31,513 --> 00:56:33,181
That is…

921
00:56:35,183 --> 00:56:38,728
a little difficult to describe

922
00:56:39,979 --> 00:56:41,147
with words.

923
00:56:43,191 --> 00:56:46,569
Hitting on women is a piece of cake.

924
00:56:47,779 --> 00:56:48,988
You see, those girls…

925
00:56:50,156 --> 00:56:51,366
They all liked me.

926
00:56:53,451 --> 00:56:54,619
I'm not sure.

927
00:56:55,578 --> 00:56:57,080
I think it's just you.

928
00:56:57,163 --> 00:57:00,125
Why won't you believe me? It's true.

929
00:57:00,208 --> 00:57:03,378
They all really liked me.

930
00:57:03,461 --> 00:57:04,671
I also think…

931
00:57:06,714 --> 00:57:08,967
you only look like a petty loser.

932
00:57:09,592 --> 00:57:10,718
Sorry for the bad news.

933
00:57:11,845 --> 00:57:12,887
We…

934
00:57:14,264 --> 00:57:15,265
do not…

935
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:18,685
believe your words.

936
00:57:20,979 --> 00:57:22,605
If they don't listen to me,

937
00:57:23,231 --> 00:57:24,274
then…

938
00:57:25,442 --> 00:57:27,193
I take off

939
00:57:28,486 --> 00:57:33,116
my necktie and bind their hands and feet.

940
00:57:33,199 --> 00:57:35,452
<i>The investigation headquarters
of the Gyeonggi Agency stated</i>

941
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:37,287
<i>they received the confession from Woo,</i>

942
00:57:37,370 --> 00:57:39,747
<i>the suspect who killed
the female university student</i>

943
00:57:39,831 --> 00:57:42,834
<i>who went missing in February,
that he killed seven and buried them</i>

944
00:57:42,917 --> 00:57:44,002
<i>until early this year.</i>

945
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:46,671
<i>Last month,</i>

946
00:57:46,754 --> 00:57:49,257
<i>he conducted two psychopathy tests</i>

947
00:57:49,883 --> 00:57:54,721
<i>and was confirmed as a typical psychopath
with scores of 27 and 28 respectively.</i>

948
00:57:57,891 --> 00:57:58,975
I will be

949
00:58:00,393 --> 00:58:01,936
sentenced to death, right?

950
00:58:02,645 --> 00:58:04,272
You should be.

951
00:58:12,155 --> 00:58:14,574
Even after I go up there, I won't find

952
00:58:15,867 --> 00:58:17,118
my peace.

953
00:58:18,703 --> 00:58:20,413
Did you dream of ending up in heaven?

954
00:58:36,471 --> 00:58:38,431
Goodness, Ji-sook.

955
00:58:38,515 --> 00:58:41,893
Ji-sook, you've returned in such vain.

956
00:59:02,914 --> 00:59:04,040
Let's go.

957
00:59:11,464 --> 00:59:13,341
GYEONGGI INVESTIGATION HEADQUARTERS
OF SERIAL MISSING WOMEN CASE

958
00:59:16,135 --> 00:59:17,220
Gil-pyo.

959
00:59:18,012 --> 00:59:18,930
A souvenir.

960
00:59:22,684 --> 00:59:25,520
Park Dae-woong! Big bear! You did it!

961
00:59:25,603 --> 00:59:26,729
Thank you.

962
00:59:28,773 --> 00:59:29,983
Good work, everyone.

963
00:59:30,066 --> 00:59:31,609
-Great job.
-Great work.

964
00:59:31,693 --> 00:59:34,821
It's sad to see you go.

965
00:59:35,446 --> 00:59:37,031
You don't look too sad.

966
00:59:37,115 --> 00:59:38,449
Tell me about it.

967
00:59:38,533 --> 00:59:40,493
Well, I may not look sad,

968
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:42,620
but I'm glad and sad to see you go.

969
00:59:42,704 --> 00:59:43,788
We'll visit.

970
00:59:43,871 --> 00:59:45,582
It only takes us 50 minutes
to get here from Seoul Agency…

971
00:59:45,665 --> 00:59:47,458
I don't expect you to come.

972
00:59:47,542 --> 00:59:50,128
You're one to talk.
I don't expect you to come either.

973
00:59:50,211 --> 00:59:53,214
If we have to meet again,
it'll have to be another case…

974
00:59:53,298 --> 00:59:55,008
Goodness, no.

975
00:59:55,091 --> 00:59:57,093
In that case, I'd rather not meet at all.

976
00:59:57,176 --> 00:59:59,721
Let's just keep our memories
deep inside, right here.

977
01:00:00,305 --> 01:00:02,599
Captain Yoon,
you should also share something.

978
01:00:10,398 --> 01:00:11,816
Let's go now.

979
01:00:12,400 --> 01:00:14,652
-Great work.
-Great job.

980
01:00:14,736 --> 01:00:17,572
-Chief Park, let's have some soju.
-Let's do that.

981
01:00:17,655 --> 01:00:18,781
Stay healthy, okay?

982
01:00:18,865 --> 01:00:20,617
Yes, be mindful of your health too.

983
01:00:20,700 --> 01:00:21,993
-Bye.
-Goodbye.

984
01:00:22,076 --> 01:00:25,413
-Let's go.
-Great job.

985
01:00:35,590 --> 01:00:38,801
Why are you moving on a day when I'm free?

986
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:41,012
Because I moved to the neighborhood
you told me to.

987
01:00:41,095 --> 01:00:43,931
I can't move here
because there are lots of robberies.

988
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:46,684
Another place is too dangerous
because of burglars.

989
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:49,187
When I see you,
I realize knowing too much can hurt.

990
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:51,272
Thanks to me,
you came to a safe neighborhood.

991
01:00:51,356 --> 01:00:54,192
According to statistics,
this area has 50 percent fewer crimes

992
01:00:54,275 --> 01:00:55,860
compared to other neighborhoods.

993
01:00:55,943 --> 01:00:58,780
And a detective of the Wide-Area
Investigation Squad is your neighbor.

994
01:00:58,863 --> 01:01:00,615
So when will Detective Nam get here?

995
01:01:00,698 --> 01:01:02,659
-Detective Nam?
-Yes.

996
01:01:02,742 --> 01:01:05,370
I have your order of beef intestines.

997
01:01:05,453 --> 01:01:07,830
-These are all mine?
-Yes.

998
01:01:09,832 --> 01:01:13,461
My gosh, this is a lot. All right.

999
01:01:13,544 --> 01:01:15,588
-Goodbye.
-Thank you.

1000
01:01:17,006 --> 01:01:18,216
Goodbye.

1001
01:01:26,974 --> 01:01:30,353
When did you get all these?

1002
01:01:30,436 --> 01:01:32,271
-I had to run.
-That looks good.

1003
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:33,606
Detective Nam got these?

1004
01:01:33,690 --> 01:01:35,525
You can get beef intestines to go?

1005
01:01:35,608 --> 01:01:37,318
Yes, you can get
just about anything to go now.

1006
01:01:37,402 --> 01:01:39,570
It's much more convenient
since it's already cooked.

1007
01:01:40,446 --> 01:01:41,322
It's really good.

1008
01:01:41,406 --> 01:01:42,782
-Is it?
-Yes, try some.

1009
01:01:42,865 --> 01:01:44,701
Let's make a toast first.

1010
01:01:45,284 --> 01:01:47,120
Congratulations.

1011
01:01:50,123 --> 01:01:52,959
This is how I recharge
the energy I lost from moving.

1012
01:02:03,261 --> 01:02:05,930
The mood here is perfect.

1013
01:02:06,013 --> 01:02:08,015
Let's get together from time to time

1014
01:02:08,099 --> 01:02:09,976
and have meetings here.

1015
01:02:10,059 --> 01:02:11,769
-It'd be nice.
-Sounds great.

1016
01:02:12,895 --> 01:02:13,896
I got it.

1017
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:17,358
Isn't this the first time we got together
outside of work?

1018
01:02:17,442 --> 01:02:19,318
-You're right.
-Is that so?

1019
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:23,239
-Oh my.
-The moon is so pretty.

1020
01:02:25,074 --> 01:02:27,910
-Yes, it's huge.
-That's very pretty.

1021
01:02:27,994 --> 01:02:29,370
-Yes.
-Right.

1022
01:02:29,454 --> 01:02:32,290
Then let's all make a wish together.

1023
01:02:33,791 --> 01:02:35,877
Woo-ju, your drinking habit
is making a wish to the moon, right?

1024
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:38,254
-You're right on.
-My gosh.

1025
01:02:38,337 --> 01:02:41,340
If Woo-ju wants to do that,
then let's make a wish.

1026
01:02:43,760 --> 01:02:45,470
